==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[reptil]]''< Old French ''[[reptile]]''< Late Latin ''[[reptile]]'', neuter of {{L.}} [[reptilis]], "[[creeping]]"< Latin ''[[repere]]'' ("to creep")< PIE [[*rep-]], "to creep, slink" (Pokorny; Watkins, 1969).

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A cold-blooded [[vertebrate]] of the Class ''[[Reptilia]].''

====Related terms====
*[[reptilia]]
*[[reptillian]]

